        "10. Use lambda expressions and the map() function to convert a list of words to upper case. For example:\n",
        "```\n",
        "seq = ['data','salt' ,'dairy','cat', 'dog']\n",
        "```\n",
        "should become:\n",
        "```\n",
        "['DATA', 'SALT', 'DAIRY', 'CAT', 'DOG']\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "seq = ['data','salt' ,'dairy','cat', 'dog']\n",
        "\n",
        "result = list(map(lambda word: word.upper(), seq))\n",
        "\n",
        "result\n"
      ],
